context: <a1_0><a1_2><b6_0>The <a1_1>mermaid<b6_0/><a1_2/><a1_1/><a1_0/> (<a0_0><a0_1><a0_2><b5_0>syrenka<b5_0/><a0_2/><a0_1/><a0_0/>) is Warsaw's symbol and can be found on statues throughout the city and on the city's coat of arms. This imagery has been in use <a2_0><b7_0>since <a2_2>at least the <a2_1>mid-14th century<b7_0/><a2_2/><a2_1/><a2_0/>. The oldest existing armed seal of Warsaw is from the year <a3_0><a3_1><a3_2><b8_0>1390<b8_0/><a3_2/><a3_1/><a3_0/>, consisting of a round seal bordered with the Latin inscription Sigilium Civitatis Varsoviensis (Seal of the city of Warsaw).
